<TITLE> Traffic halted as 3 die in Manikganj road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Manikganj, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com) Three died and 20 were injured when a bus lost control and smashed into a shop on Friday morning. The incident at Golra bus stand of Manikganj's Saturia Upazila at 9am led to traffic halt of nearly two and a half hours as angry locals took to the streets demanding speed-breakers. All the deceased were from Bahir Kamta village of the upazila. Saturia police chief Mazharul Haque, told bdnews24.com, "An Eagle Paribahan bus lost control after reaching Golra bus stand and smashed into a road-side shop. "A passer-by and two persons sitting in the shop died on spot." Agitating people of the area halted traffic on the highway demanding installation of bumps on the road. Traffic tailbacks ran five kilometres long until 11am after high officials promised the people that speed-breakers will be installed. The bodies were sent to Manikganj central hospital for autopsy, Haque said. The bus was captured but the driver managed to escape. bdnew
